Czech March Inflation Lags Central Bank Prognosis on Food Price

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-04-11T11:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/czech-march-inflation-lags-central-bank-prognosis-on-food-price.html
Czech inflation was slower than the
central bank’s forecast in March because rising global prices of
agricultural products continued to have a “limited” effect on
Czech food prices, the Czech National Bank said.  Growth of regulated prices was “slightly” slower than
expected, the bank said on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  